  "texts": [
    "HRM is often operationalized as a combination of different HRM practices together shaping the various employee relationships that exist in and around the organization (Boselie et al., 2021).",
    "Before addressing the changing role of HRM, we first must define AI because without a clear understanding of the term, it is challenging to discern how HRM practices can effectively harness its potential.",
    "Existing definitions (e.g., Afiouni, 2019; Lee et al., 2019; Schmidt et al., 2020; Mikalef and Gupta, 2021) generally converge into two main descriptions: (i) the ability to think, understand, and problem-solve like a human, and (ii) the ability to mimic human thinking.",
    "It is also important to clarify the terms \"artificial\" and \"intelligence\" when defining AI.",
    "\"Artificial\" typically encompasses anything created by humans (e.g., Simon, 1996; Mikalef and Gupta, 2021)."
  ],
